CRC Card
Class: Aircraft
Responsibilities:
- Keep track of the aircraft’s ID and type
- Maintain current flight data (altitude, speed, heading)
- Update its data when new information is received
- provide aircraft details when requested
Collaborators(if any):
- AircraftDatabase
- TransponderReceiver
Assumptions(if any):
- Each aircraft has its own unique identifier

CRC Card
Class: TransponderReceiver
Responsibilities:
- Receive broadcast signals from aircraft transponders
- Pass the incoming packets to be decoded
- Make sure the signal data is received correctly
Collaborators(if any):
- PacketDecoder
- Aircraft
Assumptions(if any):
- Aircraft continuously broadcast flight data

CRC Card 
Class: PacketDecoder
Responsibilities:
- Decode the high-density packet format sent by aircraft
- Extract useful flight data from the packet
- Convert the packet data into a format the system can use
Collaborators(if any):
- TransponderReceiver
- AircraftDatabase
Assumptions(if any):
-All packets follow the same encoding format

CRC Card
Class: AircraftDatabase
- Store records for aircraft currently being tracked
- Update aircraft information when new data arrives
- Provide aircraft information to other system components
- Keep the most recent flight data for each aircraft
Collaborators(if any):
- PacketDecoder
- DisplaySystem
- DangerDetectionSystem
- ControllerInterface
Assumptions(if any):
- The database only stores aircraft currently in the system

CRC Card
Class: DisplaySystem
Responsibilities:
- Show aircraft positions on the controller’s screen
- Show aircraft data to air traffic controllers
- Refresh the display with updated information
Collaborators(if any):
- AircraftDatabase
- DisplayUpdater
Assumptions(if any):
- Controllers use the display to monitor aircraft activity

CRC Card
Class: DisplayUpdater
Responsibilities:
- Trigger updates to the display every 10 seconds
- Retrieve latest aircraft data
- Trigger periodic display updates
Collaborators(if any):
- DisplaySystem
- AircraftDatabase
Assumptions(if any):
- Updates will occur automatically without manual input

CRC Card
Class: DangerDetectionSystem
Responsibilities:
- Analyze aircraft flight data
- Detect any potential collisions or unsafe proximity
- Generate alerts for controllers
Collaborators(if any):
- AircraftDatabase
- ControllerInterface
Assumptions(if any):
- Danger conditions include aircraft proximity or altitude conflicts

CRC Card
Class: ControllerInterface
Responsibilities:
- Allow the controller to request information about an aircraft
- Display aircraft details when selected on the screen
- Show alerts or warnings generated by the system
Collaborators(if any):
- AircraftDatabase
- DangerDetectionSystem
- DisplaySystem
Assumptions(if any):
- Controllers interact through a graphical interface

AI Usage Note:
This design was developed independently. No generative AI tools were used in producing the CRC cards.












